- You just shook his head.
- What else was I gonna to do?

23
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:09,700
Count to 53.

24
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:26,700
- Good evening, Mr. Siegel.
- Hi, give that a brush for me.

25
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:40,200
- Weren't you going to California?
- I came to give you a present.

26
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:46,000
- Present?
- Yeah, open it.

27
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:55,100
- I don't get it.
- We hired you to do a job.

28
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:59,700
We pay you a nice salary,
we throw in a piece of the action -

29
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:03,700
- and you pay us back
by stealing from us.

30
00:05:03,900 --> 00:05:08,300
Do you want the shirt off my back?
I'd be happy to give it you.

31
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:11,800
Here, from Sulka's.
They're the ones I wear.

32
00:05:11,900 --> 00:05:16,900
If I'd taken longer, I'd have
bought some pants and some suits.

33
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:23,400
But I can give you some tips.
Let me see your shoes.

34
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:29,500
I don't want to be rude to you,
but they don't go with anything.

35
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:37,000
$3,900 we paid three guys to take
care of this. Why are we here?

36
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:43,900
You know his thinking process.
Ben has only one problem.

37
00:05:44,100 --> 00:05:48,700
The same problem he had when
we were kids together on the street.

38
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:52,200
He doesn't respect money.

39
00:05:57,200 --> 00:06:04,100
But that's for summer... and you
don't have to worry about summer.

40
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:09,100
If it was just business, I'd sell
insurance or import dresses.

41
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:34,200
The key to taking over Jack Dragna's
Southern California rackets -

42
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:40,000
- is to come in smooth. Approach
him like we want to be a partner.

43
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:44,700
The guy's been running the rackets
for 20 years with no competition.

44
00:06:44,900 --> 00:06:50,800
- Except for Mickey Cohen.
- So we move in amiably.

45
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:55,500
- What about the bars and clubs?
- Fifty-fifty.

46
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:59,100
We move in,
but we don't ruin anything.

47
00:06:59,300 --> 00:07:05,500
- Joey A. Knows Jack Dragna.
- Jack's a cold-blooded killer.

48
00:07:05,700 --> 00:07:11,100
You've got to be careful. Don't say
nothing he'd take offence at.

49
00:07:11,300 --> 00:07:16,300
- What are you smiling at?
- Nothing.

50
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:22,100
- Why can't we go to California?
- Maybe next time.

51
00:07:24,100 --> 00:07:29,000
When you get to Los Angeles,
don't call George.

52
00:07:29,100 --> 00:07:33,900
He's a movie star now, and attracts
more attention than Roosevelt.

53
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:38,100
- This has to be quick and quiet.
- And amiable.

54
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:40,600
Very funny. 12 days.

55
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:46,800
Four days out. Four days
of diplomacy. Four days back.

56
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:57,100
- Ben, could I talk to you a minute?
- After I say goodbye to the family.

57
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:04,500
I'll miss you.

58
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:09,500
When I get you on the phone,
tell me what presents you want.

59
00:08:09,700 --> 00:08:15,800
- I already know what I want.
- Don't tell me now. Think about it.

60
00:08:15,900 --> 00:08:21,500
- I need money, Ben. $50,000.
- For what?

61
00:08:21,700 --> 00:08:27,300
The cops, the D.A., the FBI.
They're threatening to lock me up.

62
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:32,000
They're no good, these people,
except assistant D.A. Allen Stein.

63
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:35,300
Jewish kid.
His family's from Bedford Street.

64
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:40,100
What happened to the 50,000
for the armoured truck heist?

65
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:46,200
It's gone. You know me with money,
I blew it at the track.

66
00:08:47,100 --> 00:08:54,000
Are you saying that if you don't
get it you're going to rat on me?

67
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:59,800
You? Never. I love you, Ben.
I would never rat on you.

68
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:06,500
You ain't gonna kill me, are you?

69
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:16,400
I'm going to try very hard
to forget that this ever happened.

70
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:21,900
- I owe you my life, Ben.
- I'd say that's a fair assessment.

71
00:09:22,100 --> 00:09:25,600
Bend your knees, Harry.

72
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:31,500
When you jump from the train, bend
your knees to soften the impact.

73
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:36,600
Okay, Ben. Sure thing.

74
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:10,700
This has been four of the most
wonderful days I've ever spent.

75
00:10:10,900 --> 00:10:15,800
A lot of it
was in the motion of the train.

76
00:10:19,900 --> 00:10:26,100
He knows you. Are you somebody, too?
I love you, George.

77
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:32,600
- You look like a million bucks.
- You're looking good yourself.

78
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:37,500
Well, that's what they pay me for.
Okay, we're moving on here.

79
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:42,000
You're at the Beverly Hills Hotel,
bungalow five.

80
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:47,100
I know you said four days,
but I reserved six.

81
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:56,100
- Jack Dragna's the kingpin here.
- He runs a nice little operation.

82
00:10:56,200 --> 00:11:00,700
<i>You've got a city with 3 million
people and his operation is little?</i>

83
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:05,200
Less to worry about. I'll drop you,
then run back to the studio.

84
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:09,000
- Why don't I go with you?
- If you like.

85
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:16,300
Hank's my friend. A dame like you
will give him a lot of headaches.

86
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:20,300
- I'm on to you.
- The blueprints are all drawn.

87
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:25,000
- New cigarette.
- She's eaten a whole cigarette.

88
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:30,100
Forget that you've ever seen him.
Here, get what I mean?

89
00:11:30,300 --> 00:11:34,000
Take that money
and buy yourself some manners.

90
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:37,100
To waste on you?

91
00:11:38,300 --> 00:11:42,600
Two bucks for one beer
and some phoney champagne?

92
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:46,400
Here's half a buck.
Split it between you.

93
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:50,600
Two bucks for one beer
and some phoney champagne?

94
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:56,100
- Here's half a buck.
- You're so cheap you're wholesale.

95
00:11:57,400 --> 00:12:00,900
Don't forget, mister,
I asked you nice.

96
00:12:01,100 --> 00:12:04,400
Rolling, quiet please.

97
00:12:06,900 --> 00:12:10,600
Benny, you want to hit somebody
with a chair?

98
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:19,800
With this
I can hit home runs all night.

99
00:12:20,700 --> 00:12:26,500
- Take this in case I come back.
- Can't I have a line?

100
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:29,400
Honey, he's the star.

101
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:40,500
- That was impressive, Georgie boy.
- I'm a pro.

102
00:12:44,400 --> 00:12:47,000
May I?

103
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:50,800
If you want an answer,
finish the question.

104
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:54,600
- Light your cigarette?
- Sure.

105
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:06,500
I thought you were going to ask me
something a little more exciting.

106
00:13:06,700 --> 00:13:10,600
- Like what?
- Use your imagination.

107
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:16,300
- I'm using it.
- Let me know when you're finished.

108
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:27,400
Is she a bit player?

109
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:33,500
Flamingo? Not for Joey Adonis.
That's Virginia Hill.

110
00:13:33,700 --> 00:13:39,800
Joey's crazy. No woman is worth
a bullet between the eyes.

111
00:13:40,100 --> 00:13:43,800
It depends on whose eyes
and which woman.

112
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:54,100
Why is Ben Siegel so interested in
a gal who's going with his friend?

113
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:59,200
Joey A? He's just an associate.
Are you still going with him?

114
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:03,900
If it were New Year's Eve, he'd be
my date. Who would your date be?

115
00:14:04,100 --> 00:14:09,300
Wife. Esta. E-S-T-A.

116
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:14,900
I'll bet Esta lives her life
faithful to her one and only Ben, -

117
00:14:15,100 --> 00:14:19,100
- who plays around like a jackrabbit
and lies through his teeth.

118
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:24,900
- I don't lie to Esta.
- Do you confess your sins to her?

119
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:32,100
What exactly does Mr. Esta
want from Miss Virginia?

120
00:14:32,300 --> 00:14:39,100
Mr. Esta can't imagine anything
he doesn't want from Miss Virginia.

121
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:43,100
- Are you ready for a divorce?
- Never.

122
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:47,600
You're pretty ferocious
where Mom is concerned.

123
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:52,700
The rest of the time you're just
a sweet-talking, fuck-happy fellow -

124
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:56,800
- with some good dialogue.
Dialogue's cheap in Hollywood.

125
00:14:56,900 --> 00:15:01,300
Why don't you run outside
and jerk yourself a soda?

126
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:20,800
How would someone go about
getting a screen test done?

127
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:27,400
- Do you know someone who wants one?
- No, I'm just interested.

128
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:31,300
What about Virginia Hill?
Does she have a future in movies?

129
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:35,500
I'm not sure of my own future.
Lana Turner lives there.

130
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:40,800
Cesar Romero lives there.

131
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:45,400
Gary Cooper is there on the right.
He paid 45 grand.

132
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:49,300
- Houses bring that kind of money?
- Sure, and more.

133
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:54,000
- Who's is that?
- Lawrence... The opera singer.

134
00:15:54,100 --> 00:16:00,300
- Not Melchoir, the other guy.
- Lawrence Tibbett? Stop.

135
00:16:01,700 --> 00:16:06,400
- What are you doing?
- Paying my respects.

136
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:20,500
I'm looking for Lawrence Tibbett.
My name's Ben Siegel.

137
00:16:20,700 --> 00:16:24,700
- Is he expecting you?
- Not unless he's psychic.

138
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:29,700
Would you excuse me a moment?

139
00:16:35,300 --> 00:16:41,000
- How far is your house from here?
- Half a mile. What are you doing?

140
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:48,800
Mr. Siegel.

141
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:53,300
You have no idea
what an honour it is to meet you.

142
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:58,600
I took my family to hear you sing
"Rigoletto" at the Met last year.

143
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:04,900
- It was a great evening.
- You overwhelm me, Mr. Siegel.

144
00:17:05,100 --> 00:17:11,600
- That's beautiful.
- Are you related to Bugsy Siegel?

145
00:17:11,900 --> 00:17:15,100
- "Bugsy"? What do you mean?
- I beg your pardon.

146
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:19,800
A bug is nothing.
The word has no meaning.

147
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:23,400
A bug is a colloquialism.
It has no basis in reality.

148
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:28,000
Insects include a wide variety
of living creatures.

149
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:31,500
None of them can be called a bug!

150
00:17:31,700 --> 00:17:36,000
I certainly didn't mean
any offence, Mr. Siegel.

151
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:39,400
Mind if I look around, Larry?

152
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:45,500
- Do you mind if I call you Larry?
- All my friends call me Larry.

153
00:17:45,700 --> 00:17:50,300
- What brings you to L.A., Ben?
- Curiosity.

154
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:55,500
A wonderful house. What do you
think of the Beverly Hills Hotel?

155
00:17:55,700 --> 00:18:00,400
- It's the best hotel in town.
- A bungalow or a suite?

156
00:18:00,600 --> 00:18:06,400
- A bungalow. Which do you have?
- I don't. You do. Bungalow 5.

157
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:10,100
- I don't understand...
- I'm buying this house.

158
00:18:10,300 --> 00:18:15,400
- This house isn't for sale.
- Sure it is. Everything's for sale.

159
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:20,000
- How much do you want?
- Mr. Siegel...

160
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:23,200
- Ben.
- Ben...

161
00:18:23,300 --> 00:18:27,500
Why are you looking at me like that?
Are you going to hurt me?

162
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:32,700
I would protect you
from anyone who tried to hurt you.

163
00:18:32,900 --> 00:18:38,200
Your voice makes life justifiable.
I'm just trying to give you money.

164
00:18:38,300 --> 00:18:41,800
- What did you buy it for?
- $35,000.

165
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:46,700
But that was a few years ago.
I could probably get $40,000.

166
00:18:46,900 --> 00:18:53,000
It's not really a financial issue,
Mr. Siegel. Ben...

167
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:58,300
One, two, three, four...

168
00:18:58,400 --> 00:19:01,600
That's $50,000. Is that enough?

169
00:19:01,800 --> 00:19:08,200
This should be a pleasurable day
for the both of us. Here's $60,000.

170
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:13,100
It makes me sick inside when I don't
bring pleasure to someone I admire.

171
00:19:13,300 --> 00:19:17,400
Doesn't this bring you pleasure?
Why don't I see you smiling?

172
00:19:17,900 --> 00:19:23,100
- You spend money like crazy.
- So? It's only dirty paper.

173
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:28,000
- You'll only be here for four days.
- Maybe I'll stay a little longer.

174
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:32,500
- I've got to get to Jack Dragna's.
- I'll drive you.

175
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:35,200
No, this is business.

176
00:19:45,700 --> 00:19:49,600
- Nice car.
- Thank you.

177
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:02,700
- Louie.
- What the hell is this?

178
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:16,500
I'm looking for Jack Dragna.
I'm Ben Siegel.

179
00:20:16,700 --> 00:20:20,700
I'm Lou, Jack's brother.
I'll tell Jack you're here.

180
00:20:20,900 --> 00:20:25,700
He'll just be a few seconds.
Jack's finishing eating.

181
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:33,500
We run a smooth little operation.
With all due respect to Lansky, -

182
00:20:33,700 --> 00:20:38,200
- Luciano, Joey A., and whoever
the fuck else you represent, -

183
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:42,500
- I suggest you spend your time here
looking for broads.

184
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:48,000
We've got the finest in the world.
I understand that's what you like.

185
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:52,200
I can help you out
with phone numbers.

186
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:58,600
But if you want to do business,
I'm completely disinterested.

187
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:03,700
"Uninterested".
Disinterested means impartial.

188
00:21:03,900 --> 00:21:09,600
You've got two alternatives:
You and your guys can work for us.

189
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:13,500
Your little operation
will then be a big operation.

190
00:21:13,700 --> 00:21:19,300
20 betting parlours, not three.
Owning your own wire service.

191
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:24,000
It means taking risks.
Meyer, Charlie and I, we take 75%.

192
00:21:24,100 --> 00:21:29,100
You keep 25%, but that's got to be
three times more than you make now.

193
00:21:29,300 --> 00:21:34,300
- What's the second alternative?
- The second alternative...

194
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:37,600
The second alternative is here.

195
00:21:38,500 --> 00:21:45,400
- Squeeze the trigger and kill me.
- Kill you, that's an alternative?

196
00:21:58,300 --> 00:22:03,500
- You've an unusual sense of humour.
- What they say about you is true.

197
00:22:03,700 --> 00:22:06,500
You're out of your fucking mind.

198
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:12,000
Take another five seconds
to make your selection.

199
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:19,200
I guess that means you're working
for us. May I have my gun back?

200
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:23,000
Let's get started. Time is vicious
when taken for granted.

201
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:29,500
Bugsy, if we break off this thing
with Transcontinental...

202
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:40,100
I'll assume you didn't know
that no one calls me that.

203
00:22:40,300 --> 00:22:45,900
- Very nice meeting you, Jack.
- The fucking guy's crazy.

204
00:22:46,100 --> 00:22:52,900
- Should I shoot him in the back?
- Lansky and Luciano would flip.

205
00:22:53,100 --> 00:22:56,100
Play along.
Sooner or later he'll blow his lid.

206
00:22:56,300 --> 00:23:01,500
When we get him,
nobody will give a fuck.

207
00:23:36,700 --> 00:23:41,400
- Hello?
- Virginia, it's Ben...

208
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:50,400
Meyer, I know we said 12 days.
Things got a little complicated.

209
00:24:57,000 --> 00:25:00,500
Was that good?
You're from "The Herald", right?

210
00:25:00,700 --> 00:25:05,800
See that they run that, and not one
of those sinister mugshots.

211
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:09,400
- I'll try my best.
- I'd really appreciate it.

212
00:25:09,600 --> 00:25:13,200
- May I have the next dance?
- Charmed. Have you met Mr. Siegel?

213
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:18,200
- I've been admiring his movements.
- My husband. Count Di Frasso.

214
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:23,700
I'm surrounded by titles.
How can I pick one up?

215
00:25:23,900 --> 00:25:27,600
Darling, get him a title.
Make him a duke.

216
00:25:27,800 --> 00:25:31,800
Why not?

217
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:37,800
- Are you ready to come to Italy?
- Italy! I'll get my parachute.

218
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:40,300
